<exercise id="fs-idm116086704"><problem id="fs-idm2560400">
<para id="fs-idp107277632">Based on their positions in the periodic table, list the following atoms in order of increasing radius: Sr, Ca, Si, Cl.</para></problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm107831680"><problem id="fs-idm124732752">
<para id="fs-idm108600608">Based on their positions in the periodic table, list the following ions in order of increasing radius: K<sup>+</sup>, Ca<sup>2+</sup>, Al<sup>3+</sup>, Si<sup>4+</sup>.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-idm171686432">
<para id="fs-idm166668720">Si<sup>4+</sup> &lt; Al<sup>3+</sup> &lt; Ca<sup>2+</sup> &lt; K<sup>+</sup></para></solution></exercise>
